{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882286826,"sessionID":"ses_2852af5b2ffeze7qOU5Wyz60Zi","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad52d1d0010mIz6i9CxZcbTH","messageID":"msg_d7ad51fcc001mw0WM5gsJlQwjG","sessionID":"ses_2852af5b2ffeze7qOU5Wyz60Zi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_205be8f1780647ee8ce8d3ee","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/Makefile"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/Makefile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Makefile for AgentCube Docker builds\n2: # Provides targets for building, pushing, and managing container images\n3: \n4: # Docker configuration\n5: DOCKER_REGISTRY ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh\n6: DOCKER_TAG ?= latest\n7: VERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n8: COMMIT_SHA ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n9: \n10: # Image names\n11: WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\n12: ROUTER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router\n13: PICOD_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod\n14: \n15: # Build all images\n16: .PHONY: docker-build-all\n17: docker-build-all: docker-build-workloadmanager docker-build-router docker-build-picod\n18: \t@echo \"✓ All images built successfully\"\n19: \n20: # Build Workload Manager image\n21: .PHONY: docker-build-workloadmanager\n22: docker-build-workloadmanager:\n23: \t@echo \"Building Workload Manager image...\"\n24: \tdocker build \\\n25: \t\t-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile \\\n26: \t\t--build-arg VERSION=$(VERSION) \\\n27: \t\t--build-arg COMMIT_SHA=$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n28: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n29: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n30: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(VERSION) \\\n31: \t\t.\n32: \t@echo \"✓ Workload Manager image built: $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n33: \n34: # Build Router image\n35: .PHONY: docker-build-router\n36: docker-build-router:\n37: \t@echo \"Building Router image...\"\n38: \tdocker build \\\n39: \t\t-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n40: \t\t--build-arg VERSION=$(VERSION) \\\n41: \t\t--build-arg COMMIT_SHA=$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n42: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n43: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n44: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(VERSION) \\\n45: \t\t.\n46: \t@echo \"✓ Router image built: $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n47: \n48: # Build Picod image\n49: .PHONY: docker-build-picod\n50: docker-build-picod:\n51: \t@echo \"Building Picod image...\"\n52: \tdocker build \\\n53: \t\t-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n54: \t\t--build-arg VERSION=$(VERSION) \\\n55: \t\t--build-arg COMMIT_SHA=$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n56: \t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n57: \t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n58: \t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(VERSION) \\\n59: \t\t.\n60: \t@echo \"✓ Picod image built: $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n61: \n62: # Push all images\n63: .PHONY: docker-push-all\n64: docker-push-all: docker-push-workloadmanager docker-push-router docker-push-picod\n65: \t@echo \"✓ All images pushed successfully\"\n66: \n67: # Push Workload Manager image\n68: .PHONY: docker-push-workloadmanager\n69: docker-push-workloadmanager:\n70: \t@echo \"Pushing Workload Manager image to $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)...\"\n71: \tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n72: \tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n73: \tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(VERSION)\n74: \n75: # Push Router image\n76: .PHONY: docker-push-router\n77: docker-push-router:\n78: \t@echo \"Pushing Router image to $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)...\"\n79: \tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n80: \tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n81: \tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(VERSION)\n82: \n83: # Push Picod image\n84: .PHONY: docker-push-picod\n85: docker-push-picod:\n86: \t@echo \"Pushing Picod image to $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)...\"\n87: \tdocker push $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n88: \tdocker push $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n89: \tdocker push $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(VERSION)\n90: \n91: # Load images to Kind cluster\n92: .PHONY: kind-load-all\n93: kind-load-all: kind-load-workloadmanager kind-load-router kind-load-picod\n94: \t@echo \"✓ All images loaded to Kind cluster\"\n95: \n96: .PHONY: kind-load-workloadmanager\n97: kind-load-workloadmanager:\n98: \tkind load docker-image $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n99: \n100: .PHONY: kind-load-router\n101: kind-load-router:\n102: \tkind load docker-image $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n103: \n104: .PHONY: kind-load-picod\n105: kind-load-picod:\n106: \tkind load docker-image $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n107: \n108: # Multi-architecture build (requires Docker Buildx)\n109: .PHONY: docker-buildx-all\n110: docker-buildx-all: docker-buildx-workloadmanager docker-buildx-router docker-buildx-picod\n111: \t@echo \"✓ All multi-arch images built successfully\"\n112: \n113: .PHONY: docker-buildx-workloadmanager\n114: docker-buildx-workloadmanager:\n115: \t@echo \"Building multi-arch Workload Manager image...\"\n116: \tdocker buildx build \\\n117: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n118: \t\t-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile \\\n119: \t\t--build-arg VERSION=$(VERSION) \\\n120: \t\t--build-arg COMMIT_SHA=$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n121: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n122: \t\t--push \\\n123: \t\t.\n124: \n125: .PHONY: docker-buildx-router\n126: docker-buildx-router:\n127: \t@echo \"Building multi-arch Router image...\"\n128: \tdocker buildx build \\\n129: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n130: \t\t-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n131: \t\t--build-arg VERSION=$(VERSION) \\\n132: \t\t--build-arg COMMIT_SHA=$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n133: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n134: \t\t--push \\\n135: \t\t.\n136: \n137: .PHONY: docker-buildx-picod\n138: docker-buildx-picod:\n139: \t@echo \"Building multi-arch Picod image...\"\n140: \tdocker buildx build \\\n141: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n142: \t\t-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n143: \t\t--build-arg VERSION=$(VERSION) \\\n144: \t\t--build-arg COMMIT_SHA=$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n145: \t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n146: \t\t--push \\\n147: \t\t.\n148: \n149: # Clean up local images\n150: .PHONY: docker-clean\n151: docker-clean:\n152: \t@echo \"Cleaning up local Docker images...\"\n153: \t-docker rmi $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n154: \t-docker rmi $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) 2>/dev/null || true\n155: \t-docker rmi $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(VERSION) 2>/dev/null || true\n156: \t-docker rmi $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n157: \t-docker rmi $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) 2>/dev/null || true\n158: \t-docker rmi $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(VERSION) 2>/dev/null || true\n159: \t-docker rmi $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n160: \t-docker rmi $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) 2>/dev/null || true\n161: \t-docker rmi $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(VERSION) 2>/dev/null || true\n162: \t@echo \"✓ Cleanup complete\"\n163: \n164: # Validate images (size, security, configuration)\n165: .PHONY: docker-validate\n166: docker-validate: docker-validate-workloadmanager docker-validate-router docker-validate-picod\n167: \t@echo \"✓ All images validated successfully\"\n168: \n169: .PHONY: docker-validate-workloadmanager\n170: docker-validate-workloadmanager:\n171: \t@echo \"Validating Workload Manager image...\"\n172: \t@./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n173: \n174: .PHONY: docker-validate-router\n175: docker-validate-router:\n176: \t@echo \"Validating Router image...\"\n177: \t@./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n178: \n179: .PHONY: docker-validate-picod\n180: docker-validate-picod:\n181: \t@echo \"Validating Picod image...\"\n182: \t@./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n183: \n184: # Run all tests\n185: .PHONY: docker-test\n186: docker-test: docker-test-build docker-test-runtime\n187: \t@echo \"✓ All Docker tests passed\"\n188: \n189: .PHONY: docker-test-build\n190: docker-test-build:\n191: \t@echo \"Running build tests...\"\n192: \t@./deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh\n193: \n194: .PHONY: docker-test-runtime\n195: docker-test-runtime:\n196: \t@echo \"Running runtime tests...\"\n197: \t@./deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh\n198: \n199: # Help target\n200: .PHONY: help\n201: help:\n202: \t@echo \"AgentCube Docker Makefile\"\n203: \t@echo \"\"\n204: \t@echo \"Build targets:\"\n205: \t@echo \"  docker-build-all              - Build all three images\"\n206: \t@echo \"  docker-build-workloadmanager  - Build Workload Manager image\"\n207: \t@echo \"  docker-build-router           - Build Router image\"\n208: \t@echo \"  docker-build-picod            - Build Picod image\"\n209: \t@echo \"\"\n210: \t@echo \"Push targets:\"\n211: \t@echo \"  docker-push-all               - Push all images to registry\"\n212: \t@echo \"  docker-push-workloadmanager   - Push Workload Manager image\"\n213: \t@echo \"  docker-push-router            - Push Router image\"\n214: \t@echo \"  docker-push-picod             - Push Picod image\"\n215: \t@echo \"\"\n216: \t@echo \"Kind targets:\"\n217: \t@echo \"  kind-load-all                 - Load all images to Kind cluster\"\n218: \t@echo \"  kind-load-workloadmanager     - Load Workload Manager image\"\n219: \t@echo \"  kind-load-router              - Load Router image\"\n220: \t@echo \"  kind-load-picod               - Load Picod image\"\n221: \t@echo \"\"\n222: \t@echo \"Multi-arch targets:\"\n223: \t@echo \"  docker-buildx-all             - Build multi-arch images (amd64, arm64)\"\n224: \t@echo \"  docker-buildx-workloadmanager - Build multi-arch Workload Manager\"\n225: \t@echo \"  docker-buildx-router          - Build multi-arch Router\"\n226: \t@echo \"  docker-buildx-picod           - Build multi-arch Picod\"\n227: \t@echo \"\"\n228: \t@echo \"Test & validate targets:\"\n229: \t@echo \"  docker-test                   - Run all Docker tests\"\n230: \t@echo \"  docker-validate               - Validate all images\"\n231: \t@echo \"  docker-clean                  - Clean up local images\"\n232: \t@echo \"\"\n233: \t@echo \"Variables:\"\n234: \t@echo \"  DOCKER_REGISTRY=$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)\"\n235: \t@echo \"  DOCKER_TAG=$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n236: \t@echo \"  VERSION=$(VERSION)\"\n237: \t@echo \"  COMMIT_SHA=$(COMMIT_SHA)\"\n\n(End of file - total 237 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Makefile for AgentCube Docker builds\n# Provides targets for building, pushing, and managing container images\n\n# Docker configuration\nDOCKER_REGISTRY ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh\nDOCKER_TAG ?= latest\nVERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\nCOMMIT_SHA ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n\n# Image names\nWORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\nROUTER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router\nPICOD_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod\n\n# Build all images\n.PHONY: docker-build-all\ndocker-build-all: docker-build-workloadmanager docker-build-router docker-build-picod\n\t@echo \"✓ All images built successfully\"\n\n# Build Workload Manager image","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/Makefile","time":{"start":1775882286807,"end":1775882286824}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882286832,"sessionID":"ses_2852af5b2ffeze7qOU5Wyz60Zi","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad53205001zK2quoPVpBf9Rq","messageID":"msg_d7ad51fcc001mw0WM5gsJlQwjG","sessionID":"ses_2852af5b2ffeze7qOU5Wyz60Zi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_62b81dffeeb84ae48ca459bf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `docker`  \n6: **Language:** Dockerfile  \n7: **Size:** S  \n8: **Type:** Multi-stage Docker build for Workload Manager, Router, and picod container images\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-032.1: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile` for building the Workload Manager container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Build stage configuration\n21: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` is built with repository root as context\n22: - **WHEN** the build stage runs\n23: - **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base image\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Go module cache optimization\n26: - **GIVEN** go.mod and go.sum files exist\n27: - **WHEN** the build stage copies dependencies\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first and run `go mod download` before copying source code\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Workload Manager binary compilation\n31: - **GIVEN** source code is copied to builder\n32: - **WHEN** build runs\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL compile with `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o /workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Runtime stage base image\n36: - **GIVEN** build stage completes\n37: - **WHEN** runtime stage begins\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as minimal runtime base image\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Non-root user creation\n41: - **GIVEN** runtime stage starts\n42: - **WHEN** image is prepared\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL create non-root user `apiserver` with UID 1000\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Binary copy to runtime image\n46: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager binary is built\n47: - **WHEN** runtime stage copies artifacts\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL copy binary from builder stage to `/workloadmanager`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Container port exposure\n51: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n52: - **WHEN** container runs\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL expose port 8080\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Default command configuration\n56: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n57: - **WHEN** container starts without override\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL run `/workloadmanager` as entrypoint\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### REQ-032.2: Router Dockerfile\n63: \n64: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.router` for building the Router container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Build stage configuration\n67: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router` is built with repository root as context\n68: - **WHEN** the build stage runs\n69: - **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base image\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Go module cache optimization\n72: - **GIVEN** go.mod and go.sum files exist\n73: - **WHEN** the build stage copies dependencies\n74: - **THEN** it SHALL copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first and run `go mod download` before copying source code\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Router binary compilation\n77: - **GIVEN** source code is copied to builder\n78: - **WHEN** build runs\n79: - **THEN** it SHALL compile with `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o /router ./cmd/router`\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Runtime stage base image\n82: - **GIVEN** build stage completes\n83: - **WHEN** runtime stage begins\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as minimal runtime base image\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Non-root user creation\n87: - **GIVEN** runtime stage starts\n88: - **WHEN** image is prepared\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL create non-root user `router` with UID 1000\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Binary copy to runtime image\n92: - **GIVEN** router binary is built\n93: - **WHEN** runtime stage copies artifacts\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL copy binary from builder stage to `/router`\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Container port exposure\n97: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n98: - **WHEN** container runs\n99: - **THEN** it SHALL expose port 8080\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Default command configuration\n102: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n103: - **WHEN** container starts without override\n104: - **THEN** it SHALL run `/router` as entrypoint\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### REQ-032.3: Picod Dockerfile\n109: \n110: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.picod` for building the picod container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Build stage configuration\n113: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod` is built with repository root as context\n114: - **WHEN** the build stage runs\n115: - **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base image\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Go module cache optimization\n118: - **GIVEN** go.mod and go.sum files exist\n119: - **WHEN** the build stage copies dependencies\n120: - **THEN** it SHALL copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first and run `go mod download` before copying source code\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Picod binary compilation\n123: - **GIVEN** source code is copied to builder\n124: - **WHEN** build runs\n125: - **THEN** it SHALL compile with `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o /picod ./cmd/picod`\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Runtime stage base image\n128: - **GIVEN** build stage completes\n129: - **WHEN** runtime stage begins\n130: - **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as minimal runtime base image\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Non-root user creation\n133: - **GIVEN** runtime stage starts\n134: - **WHEN** image is prepared\n135: - **THEN** it SHALL create non-root user `picod` with UID 1000\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: Binary copy to runtime image\n138: - **GIVEN** picod binary is built\n139: - **WHEN** runtime stage copies artifacts\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL copy binary from builder stage to `/picod`\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: Container port exposure\n143: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n144: - **WHEN** container runs\n145: - **THEN** it SHALL expose port 8080\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Default command configuration\n148: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n149: - **WHEN** container starts without override\n150: - **THEN** it SHALL run `/picod` as entrypoint\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ### REQ-032.4: Multi-stage Build Optimization\n155: \n156: **Requirement:** The system SHALL optimize Docker images for size and security through multi-stage build patterns.\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: Minimal runtime image\n159: - **GIVEN** multi-stage build completes\n160: - **WHEN** final image size is measured\n161: - **THEN** it SHALL be under 50MB for each component (Workload Manager, Router, picod)\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: No build tools in runtime\n164: - **GIVEN** runtime stage completes\n165: - **WHEN** image is inspected\n166: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT contain go compiler, git, or build dependencies\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: Static binary linkage\n169: - **GIVEN** CGO_ENABLED=0 is set during build\n170: - **WHEN** binary runs in runtime stage\n171: - **THEN** it SHALL have no dynamic library dependencies\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Alpine base image\n174: - **GIVEN** runtime stage uses alpine:3.19\n175: - **WHEN** image is scanned for vulnerabilities\n176: - **THEN** it SHALL have minimal CVE surface compared to Debian-based images\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ### REQ-032.5: Security Best Practices\n181: \n182: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement container security best practices in all Dockerfiles.\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: Non-root user execution\n185: - **GIVEN** container starts\n186: - **WHEN** process runs\n187: - **THEN** it SHALL run as non-root user (UID 1000)\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Read-only filesystem compatibility\n190: - **GIVEN** container runs with read-only root filesystem\n191: - **WHEN** application needs temporary storage\n192: - **THEN** it SHALL use `/tmp` volume mount if needed\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: No secrets in image\n195: - **GIVEN** Dockerfile is built\n196: - **WHEN** image layers are inspected\n197: - **THEN** they SHALL NOT contain hardcoded credentials, tokens, or API keys\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: Minimal attack surface\n200: - **GIVEN** runtime image is built\n201: - **WHEN** shell access is attempted\n202: - **THEN** image MAY exclude `/bin/sh` to prevent shell injection (optional hardening)\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ### REQ-032.6: Build Context and .dockerignore\n207: \n208: **Requirement:** The system SHALL use efficient build context by excluding unnecessary files via `.dockerignore`.\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Exclude .git directory\n211: - **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` exists\n212: - **WHEN** build context is sent to Docker daemon\n213: - **THEN** `.git/` directory SHALL be excluded\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: Exclude build artifacts\n216: - **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` exists\n217: - **WHEN** build context is sent\n218: - **THEN** `bin/`, `pkg/`, and `*_test.go` files SHALL be excluded from context\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Exclude development files\n221: - **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` exists\n222: - **WHEN** build context is sent\n223: - **THEN** `.md` files (except README if needed), `.gitignore`, and editor files SHALL be excluded\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Include only required files\n226: - **GIVEN** `.dockerignore` is configured\n227: - **WHEN** build runs\n228: - **THEN** context SHALL include only: `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `cmd/`, `pkg/`, and any required configs\n229: \n230: ---\n231: \n232: ### REQ-032.7: Makefile Integration\n233: \n234: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building all three Docker images.\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: Build Workload Manager image\n237: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-workloadmanager` target\n238: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-workloadmanager` runs\n239: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged `workloadmanager:latest` using `docker/Dockerfile`\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Build Router image\n242: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-router` target\n243: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-router` runs\n244: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged `router:latest` using `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: Build picod image\n247: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-picod` target\n248: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-picod` runs\n249: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged `picod:latest` using `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Build all images\n252: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-build-all` target\n253: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-all` runs\n254: - **THEN** it SHALL build all three images sequentially\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Push Workload Manager image\n257: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-push-workloadmanager` target with `REGISTRY` variable\n258: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-workloadmanager REGISTRY=registry.example.com` runs\n259: - **THEN** it SHALL tag and push image to `registry.example.com/workloadmanager:latest`\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: Push all images\n262: - **GIVEN** Makefile has `docker-push-all` target with `REGISTRY` variable\n263: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-all REGISTRY=registry.example.com` runs\n264: - **THEN** it SHALL tag and push all three images to specified registry\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ## Data Types\n269: \n270: ```dockerfile\n271: # Docker build arguments (common to all Dockerfiles)\n272: ARG GO_VERSION=1.21\n273: ARG ALPINE_VERSION=3.19\n274: ARG TARGETARCH=amd64\n275: \n276: # Labels for image metadata\n277: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"<component>\"\n278: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube <component> component\"\n279: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n280: ```\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## File Structure\n285: \n286: ```\n287: docker/\n288: ├── Dockerfile           # Workload Manager image\n289: ├── Dockerfile.router    # Router image\n290: ├── Dockerfile.picod     # Picod image\n291: └── .dockerignore        # Build context exclusions (shared or per-Dockerfile)\n292: ```\n293: \n294: ---\n295: \n296: ## Make Targets\n297: \n298: | Target | Description |\n299: |--------|-------------|\n300: | `docker-build-workloadmanager` | Build Workload Manager image |\n301: | `docker-build-router` | Build Router image |\n302: | `docker-build-picod` | Build picod image |\n303: | `docker-build-all` | Build all three images |\n304: | `docker-push-workloadmanager` | Push Workload Manager image to registry |\n305: | `docker-push-router` | Push Router image to registry |\n306: | `docker-push-picod` | Push picod image to registry |\n307: | `docker-push-all` | Push all images to registry |\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ## Environment Variables\n312: \n313: | Variable | Component | Purpose | Default |\n314: |----------|-----------|---------|---------|\n315: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis server address | - |\n316: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis authentication | \"\" |\n317: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager endpoint | - |\n318: | `PORT` | All | HTTP listen port | 8080 |\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: ## Acceptance Checklist\n323: \n324: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile` — Workload Manager multi-stage build\n325: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.router` — Router multi-stage build\n326: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.picod` — Picod multi-stage build\n327: - [ ] `docker/.dockerignore` — Build context optimization\n328: - [ ] Make targets for building all three images\n329: - [ ] Make targets for pushing images to registry\n330: - [ ] Non-root user in all runtime images\n331: - [ ] Alpine 3.19 base for minimal image size\n332: - [ ] CGO disabled for static binaries\n333: - [ ] Port 8080 exposed in all images\n334: - [ ] Image size under 50MB each\n335: - [ ] OCI labels for image metadata\n336: - [ ] Go module cache optimization (go.mod copied first)\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ## Open Questions\n341: \n342: 1. Should Dockerfiles support multi-architecture builds (ARM64, AMD64) via `--platform` flag?\n343: 2. Should health check instructions (`HEALTHCHECK`) be added to Dockerfiles?\n344: 3. Should distroless images be used instead of Alpine for enhanced security?\n345: 4. Should build version/commit be injected into images via `ARG` at build time?\n346: \n347: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 347 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `docker`  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Size:** S  \n**Type:** Multi-stage Docker build for Workload Manager, Router, and picod container images\n\n**Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-032.1: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile` for building the Workload Manager container image using multi-stage build with separate build and runtime stages.\n\n#### Scenario: Build stage configuration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882286810,"end":1775882286829}}}}
