{"type":"text","timestamp":1775882307721,"sessionID":"ses_2852af5b2ffeze7qOU5Wyz60Zi","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad57f88001TpEca3fqEvnoyA","messageID":"msg_d7ad5719b001xRWuTGdmpvUDqj","sessionID":"ses_2852af5b2ffeze7qOU5Wyz60Zi","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information needed to write the delta-spec.md for AR-033. Let me create it based on the existing Makefile structure and the proposal requirements.","time":{"start":1775882307720,"end":1775882307720}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882411039,"sessionID":"ses_2852af5b2ffeze7qOU5Wyz60Zi","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad5888a001WPt7PuoCriuEVP","messageID":"msg_d7ad5719b001xRWuTGdmpvUDqj","sessionID":"ses_2852af5b2ffeze7qOU5Wyz60Zi","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_5cf636c8764e44799026fbca","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/spec/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification — AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `root`  \n**Language:** Makefile  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Makefile target system for Docker image build, push, validate, test lifecycle management\n\n**Base Specs:** design.md, deployment/docker/delta-spec.md (AR-032)\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-033.1: Build Targets (docker-build-*)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building Docker images for all components (Workload Manager, Router, Picod).\n\n#### Scenario: Build all images\n- **GIVEN** Makefile exists with `docker-build-all` target\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-all` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build all three images (workloadmanager, router, picod) sequentially\n\n#### Scenario: Build Workload Manager image\n- **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/Dockerfile` exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-workloadmanager` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged with `$(DOCKER_TAG)`, `$(COMMIT_SHA)`, and `$(VERSION)`\n\n#### Scenario: Build Router image\n- **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router` exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-router` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged with `$(DOCKER_TAG)`, `$(COMMIT_SHA)`, and `$(VERSION)`\n\n#### Scenario: Build Picod image\n- **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod` exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-picod` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged with `$(DOCKER_TAG)`, `$(COMMIT_SHA)`, and `$(VERSION)`\n\n#### Scenario: Default registry configuration\n- **GIVEN** no `DOCKER_REGISTRY` variable is set\n- **WHEN** any build target runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL use default registry `ghcr.io/volcano-sh`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom registry override\n- **GIVEN** `DOCKER_REGISTRY=registry.example.com` is set\n- **WHEN** build target runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL use custom registry in image name\n\n#### Scenario: Default tag configuration\n- **GIVEN** no `DOCKER_TAG` variable is set\n- **WHEN** any build target runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL use default tag `latest`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom tag override\n- **GIVEN** `DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0` is set\n- **WHEN** build target runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL use custom tag in image name\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.2: Push Targets (docker-push-*)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for pushing Docker images to container registry.\n\n#### Scenario: Push all images\n- **GIVEN** images are built and `docker-push-all` target exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-push-all` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL push all three images to registry\n\n#### Scenario: Push Workload Manager image\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager image is built\n- **WHEN** `make docker-push-workloadmanager` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL push all three tags (latest, commit-sha, version) to registry\n\n#### Scenario: Push Router image\n- **GIVEN** router image is built\n- **WHEN** `make docker-push-router` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL push all three tags (latest, commit-sha, version) to registry\n\n#### Scenario: Push Picod image\n- **GIVEN** picod image is built\n- **WHEN** `make docker-push-picod` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL push all three tags (latest, commit-sha, version) to registry\n\n#### Scenario: Push with custom registry\n- **GIVEN** `DOCKER_REGISTRY=registry.example.com` is set\n- **WHEN** push target runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL push to specified custom registry\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.3: Kind Load Targets (kind-load-*)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for loading Docker images to local Kind Kubernetes cluster.\n\n#### Scenario: Load all images to Kind\n- **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and images are built\n- **WHEN** `make kind-load-all` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL load all three images to Kind cluster\n\n#### Scenario: Load Workload Manager image to Kind\n- **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and workloadmanager image is built\n- **WHEN** `make kind-load-workloadmanager` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL load workloadmanager image with `$(DOCKER_TAG)` to Kind\n\n#### Scenario: Load Router image to Kind\n- **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and router image is built\n- **WHEN** `make kind-load-router` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL load router image with `$(DOCKER_TAG)` to Kind\n\n#### Scenario: Load Picod image to Kind\n- **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and picod image is built\n- **WHEN** `make kind-load-picod` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL load picod image with `$(DOCKER_TAG)` to Kind\n\n#### Scenario: Kind not installed\n- **GIVEN** Kind is not installed on the system\n- **WHEN** `make kind-load-all` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about Kind not found\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.4: Multi-architecture Build Targets (docker-buildx-*)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building multi-architecture Docker images using Docker Buildx.\n\n#### Scenario: Build all multi-arch images\n- **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available and `docker-buildx-all` target exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-all` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build multi-arch images for all three components\n\n#### Scenario: Build Workload Manager multi-arch image\n- **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available\n- **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-workloadmanager` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build image for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms and push to registry\n\n#### Scenario: Build Router multi-arch image\n- **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available\n- **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-router` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build image for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms and push to registry\n\n#### Scenario: Build Picod multi-arch image\n- **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available\n- **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-picod` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build image for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms and push to registry\n\n#### Scenario: Buildx not available\n- **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is not installed\n- **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-all` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about buildx not found\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.5: Validate Targets (docker-validate-*)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for validating Docker images against quality standards (size, layers, security, ports).\n\n#### Scenario: Validate all images\n- **GIVEN** images are built and `docker-validate` target exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-validate` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run validation script against all three images\n\n#### Scenario: Validate Workload Manager image\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager image is built\n- **WHEN** `make docker-validate-workloadmanager` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` against the image\n\n#### Scenario: Validate Router image\n- **GIVEN** router image is built\n- **WHEN** `make docker-validate-router` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` against the image\n\n#### Scenario: Validate Picod image\n- **GIVEN** picod image is built\n- **WHEN** `make docker-validate-picod` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` against the image\n\n#### Scenario: Validation script not found\n- **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `make docker-validate` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about missing script\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.6: Test Targets (docker-test-*)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for running Docker build and runtime tests.\n\n#### Scenario: Run all Docker tests\n- **GIVEN** `docker-test` target exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-test` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run both `docker-test-build` and `docker-test-runtime`\n\n#### Scenario: Run build tests\n- **GIVEN** `docker-test-build` target exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-test-build` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh`\n\n#### Scenario: Run runtime tests\n- **GIVEN** `docker-test-runtime` target exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-test-runtime` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh`\n\n#### Scenario: Test script not found\n- **GIVEN** test script does not exist\n- **WHEN** corresponding test target is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about missing script\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.7: Clean Target (docker-clean)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make target for cleaning up local Docker images.\n\n#### Scenario: Clean all local images\n- **GIVEN** local images exist and `docker-clean` target exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-clean` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL remove all local tags for workloadmanager, router, and picod images\n\n#### Scenario: Clean with missing images\n- **GIVEN** some images do not exist locally\n- **WHEN** `make docker-clean` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT fail and SHALL silently skip missing images\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.8: Help Target (help)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `help` target that prints available Make targets and their descriptions.\n\n#### Scenario: Display help information\n- **GIVEN** `help` target exists in Makefile\n- **WHEN** `make help` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL print all available targets grouped by category (build, push, kind, buildx, test, validate, clean)\n\n#### Scenario: Display variable values\n- **GIVEN** `help` target is executed\n- **WHEN** help output is printed\n- **THEN** it SHALL show current values of `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`, `VERSION`, and `COMMIT_SHA`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.9: Validation Script (validate.sh)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` script for validating Docker images.\n\n#### Scenario: Validate image size\n- **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n- **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs against the image\n- **THEN** it SHALL check that image size is under 50MB\n\n#### Scenario: Validate layer count\n- **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n- **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL check that image has 5 or fewer layers\n\n#### Scenario: Validate non-root user\n- **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n- **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL check that image specifies non-root user (not root)\n\n#### Scenario: Validate port exposure\n- **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n- **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL check that port 8080 is exposed\n\n#### Scenario: Validate health check\n- **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n- **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL check that HEALTHCHECK instruction is configured\n\n#### Scenario: Image not found\n- **GIVEN** the specified image does not exist\n- **WHEN** `validate.sh` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL exit with error code and message \"Image not found\"\n\n#### Scenario: Script is executable\n- **GIVEN** `validate.sh` file exists\n- **WHEN** file permissions are checked\n- **THEN** it SHALL have execute permission (`chmod +x`)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.10: Build Test Script (build_test.sh)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh` script for testing Docker build process.\n\n#### Scenario: Check Dockerfile existence\n- **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n- **WHEN** it checks for Dockerfiles\n- **THEN** it SHALL verify `Dockerfile`, `Dockerfile.router`, and `Dockerfile.picod` exist\n\n#### Scenario: Check Makefile targets\n- **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n- **WHEN** it checks Makefile targets\n- **THEN** it SHALL verify `docker-build-all` target is available\n\n#### Scenario: Check Docker daemon\n- **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n- **WHEN** it checks Docker daemon\n- **THEN** it SHALL verify Docker daemon is running\n\n#### Scenario: Check buildx availability\n- **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n- **WHEN** it checks buildx\n- **THEN** it SHALL verify Docker buildx is available (optional, non-fatal)\n\n#### Scenario: Script is executable\n- **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` file exists\n- **WHEN** file permissions are checked\n- **THEN** it SHALL have execute permission (`chmod +x`)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.11: Runtime Test Script (runtime_test.sh)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh` script for testing Docker container runtime behavior.\n\n#### Scenario: Test container startup\n- **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs and test image exists\n- **WHEN** it attempts container startup\n- **THEN** it SHALL verify container starts successfully\n\n#### Scenario: Test health check configuration\n- **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n- **WHEN** it checks health check\n- **THEN** it SHALL verify HEALTHCHECK is configured in image\n\n#### Scenario: Test port exposure\n- **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n- **WHEN** it checks ports\n- **THEN** it SHALL verify port 8080 is exposed\n\n#### Scenario: Test non-root user\n- **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n- **WHEN** it checks user configuration\n- **THEN** it SHALL verify container runs as non-root user\n\n#### Scenario: Image not available\n- **GIVEN** test image does not exist locally\n- **WHEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL gracefully skip tests with warning messages (non-fatal)\n\n#### Scenario: Script is executable\n- **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` file exists\n- **WHEN** file permissions are checked\n- **THEN** it SHALL have execute permission (`chmod +x`)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.12: Version and Commit Variables\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL automatically derive VERSION and COMMIT_SHA from git for use in image tagging.\n\n#### Scenario: Derive VERSION from git tags\n- **GIVEN** repository has git tags\n- **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `VERSION` variable\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `git describe --tags --always --dirty` output\n\n#### Scenario: Fallback VERSION for no tags\n- **GIVEN** repository has no git tags\n- **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `VERSION` variable\n- **THEN** it SHALL fallback to `dev`\n\n#### Scenario: Derive COMMIT_SHA from git\n- **GIVEN** repository is a valid git repo\n- **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `COMMIT_SHA` variable\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `git rev-parse --short HEAD` output\n\n#### Scenario: Fallback COMMIT_SHA for non-git\n- **GIVEN** not in a git repository\n- **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `COMMIT_SHA` variable\n- **THEN** it SHALL fallback to `unknown`\n\n#### Scenario: Override VERSION from environment\n- **GIVEN** `VERSION` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** Makefile is invoked\n- **THEN** it SHALL use environment variable value\n\n#### Scenario: Override COMMIT_SHA from environment\n- **GIVEN** `COMMIT_SHA` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** Makefile is invoked\n- **THEN** it SHALL use environment variable value\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.13: Image Name Configuration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide consistent image naming convention for all components.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager image name\n- **GIVEN** Makefile is evaluated\n- **WHEN** `WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE` variable is expanded\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager`\n\n#### Scenario: Router image name\n- **GIVEN** Makefile is evaluated\n- **WHEN** `ROUTER_IMAGE` variable is expanded\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router`\n\n#### Scenario: Picod image name\n- **GIVEN** Makefile is evaluated\n- **WHEN** `PICOD_IMAGE` variable is expanded\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.14: PHONY Target Declarations\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL declare all Make targets as `.PHONY` to prevent conflicts with files of the same name.\n\n#### Scenario: All targets declared as PHONY\n- **GIVEN** Makefile exists\n- **WHEN** `.PHONY` declarations are inspected\n- **THEN** all targets (docker-build-*, docker-push-*, kind-load-*, docker-buildx-*, docker-validate-*, docker-test-*, docker-clean, help) SHALL be declared as `.PHONY`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-033.15: Error Handling\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL handle errors gracefully in Make targets and scripts.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker command failure\n- **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running\n- **WHEN** a build target is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL fail with clear error message about Docker not being available\n\n#### Scenario: Clean target with missing images\n- **GIVEN** some images do not exist\n- **WHEN** `make docker-clean` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT fail (uses `-` prefix to ignore errors)\n\n#### Scenario: Missing Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** Dockerfile does not exist\n- **WHEN** build target runs\n- **THEN** Docker build command SHALL fail with appropriate error\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n```makefile\n# Makefile variables\nDOCKER_REGISTRY := ghcr.io/volcano-sh     # Default container registry\nDOCKER_TAG := latest                       # Default image tag\nVERSION := $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\nCOMMIT_SHA := $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n\n# Image names (constructed)\nWORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\nROUTER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router\nPICOD_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nproject-root/\n├── Makefile                              # Main Makefile with all targets\n├── deployment/\n│   └── docker/\n│       ├── Dockerfile                    # Workload Manager Dockerfile (AR-032)\n│       ├── Dockerfile.router             # Router Dockerfile (AR-032)\n│       ├── Dockerfile.picod              # Picod Dockerfile (AR-032)\n│       └── test/\n│           ├── validate.sh               # Image validation script (new)\n│           ├── build_test.sh             # Build test script (new)\n│           └── runtime_test.sh           # Runtime test script (new)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Make Targets\n\n| Target | Category | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| `docker-build-all` | Build | Build all three Docker images |\n| `docker-build-workloadmanager` | Build | Build Workload Manager image |\n| `docker-build-router` | Build | Build Router image |\n| `docker-build-picod` | Build | Build Picod image |\n| `docker-push-all` | Push | Push all images to registry |\n| `docker-push-workloadmanager` | Push | Push Workload Manager image |\n| `docker-push-router` | Push | Push Router image |\n| `docker-push-picod` | Push | Push Picod image |\n| `kind-load-all` | Kind | Load all images to Kind cluster |\n| `kind-load-workloadmanager` | Kind | Load Workload Manager image to Kind |\n| `kind-load-router` | Kind | Load Router image to Kind |\n| `kind-load-picod` | Kind | Load Picod image to Kind |\n| `docker-buildx-all` | Buildx | Build multi-arch images (amd64, arm64) |\n| `docker-buildx-workloadmanager` | Buildx | Build multi-arch Workload Manager |\n| `docker-buildx-router` | Buildx | Build multi-arch Router |\n| `docker-buildx-picod` | Buildx | Build multi-arch Picod |\n| `docker-validate` | Validate | Validate all images |\n| `docker-validate-workloadmanager` | Validate | Validate Workload Manager image |\n| `docker-validate-router` | Validate | Validate Router image |\n| `docker-validate-picod` | Validate | Validate Picod image |\n| `docker-test` | Test | Run all Docker tests |\n| `docker-test-build` | Test | Run build tests |\n| `docker-test-runtime` | Test | Run runtime tests |\n| `docker-clean` | Clean | Clean up local images |\n| `help` | Help | Print available targets and variables |\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Purpose | Default | Overridable |\n|----------|---------|---------|-------------|\n| `DOCKER_REGISTRY` | Container registry URL | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` | Yes |\n| `DOCKER_TAG` | Default image tag | `latest` | Yes |\n| `VERSION` | Git-derived version | `git describe` or `dev` | Yes |\n| `COMMIT_SHA` | Git commit short hash | `git rev-parse` or `unknown` | Yes |\n| `TEST_IMAGE` | Test image for runtime tests | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest` | Yes |\n\n---\n\n## Script Interfaces\n\n### validate.sh\n\n```bash\n# Usage\n./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh <image-name>\n\n# Exit codes\n0 - All validations passed\n1 - Validation failed or image not found\n\n# Validations performed\n- Image existence check\n- Image size < 50MB\n- Layer count <= 5\n- Non-root user specified\n- Port 8080 exposed\n- Health check configured\n```\n\n### build_test.sh\n\n```bash\n# Usage\n./deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh\n\n# Exit codes\n0 - All build tests passed\n1 - Test failed\n\n# Tests performed\n- Dockerfile existence check (3 files)\n- Makefile target availability\n- Docker daemon running check\n- Docker buildx availability (optional)\n```\n\n### runtime_test.sh\n\n```bash\n# Usage\n./deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh\n\n# Exit codes\n0 - All runtime tests completed\n1 - Critical test failed\n\n# Tests performed\n- Container startup test\n- Health check configuration check\n- Port exposure check\n- Non-root user check\n```\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `Makefile` — Contains all build, push, kind, buildx, validate, test, clean, and help targets\n- [ ] `Makefile` — All targets declared as `.PHONY`\n- [ ] `Makefile` — Variables `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`, `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA` defined\n- [ ] `Makefile` — Image name variables for all three components\n- [ ] `make help` — Prints all available targets and current variable values\n- [ ] `make docker-build-all` — Builds all three images successfully\n- [ ] `make docker-push-all` — Pushes all images (with valid credentials)\n- [ ] `make kind-load-all` — Loads images to Kind cluster (with Kind installed)\n- [ ] `make docker-buildx-all` — Builds multi-arch images (with buildx available)\n- [ ] `make docker-validate` — Validates all images\n- [ ] `make docker-test` — Runs all tests\n- [ ] `make docker-clean` — Cleans up local images\n- [ ] `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` — Exists and is executable\n- [ ] `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh` — Exists and is executable\n- [ ] `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh` — Exists and is executable\n- [ ] `validate.sh` — Checks image size, layers, user, ports, healthcheck\n- [ ] `build_test.sh` — Checks Dockerfiles, Makefile targets, Docker daemon\n- [ ] `runtime_test.sh` — Tests container runtime behavior\n- [ ] VERSION variable — Derived from git tags with fallback to `dev`\n- [ ] COMMIT_SHA variable — Derived from git with fallback to `unknown`\n- [ ] Variables overridable — Can be set from environment or command line\n- [ ] Error handling — Clean target ignores missing images gracefully\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should Windows support be added via PowerShell scripts or WSL-only?\n2. Should cosign image signing be integrated into push targets?\n3. Should remote Docker daemon support (DOCKER_HOST) be explicitly documented?\n4. Should additional validation checks be added (e.g., vulnerability scanning with Trivy)?\n5. Should a `make ci` target be added that chains test → build → validate?\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/spec/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/spec/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882411024,"end":1775882411035}}}}
